quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Working with Files[/h1]

The [b]java.io[/b] package includes a [b]File [/b]class that allows you to work with files.
To start, create a [b]File [/b]object and specify the path of the file in the constructor. [code format="java"][b]import java.io.File;[/b]
...
[b]File [/b]file = new [b]File[/b]("C:\\data\\input-file.txt");[/code]
With the [b]exists[/b]() method, you can determine whether a file exists.[code format="java"]import java.io.File;

public class MyClass {
  public static void main(String[ ] args) {
    File x = new File("C:\\sololearn\\test.txt");
    if(x.[b]exists[/b]()) {
     System.out.println(x.getName() +  "exists!");
    }
    else { 
     System.out.println("The file does not exist");
    }
  }
}[/code]
The code above prints a message stating whether or not the file exists at the specified path.
[note]The [b]getName[/b]() method returns the name of the file.
Note that we used double backslashes in the path, as one backslash should be escaped in the path String.[/note]
